<p>Chris is an Educational Psychologist who works with the most disadvantaged members of society; those whose voices are ignored or minimised in public debate. His doctorate thesis and published articles shine a light on how the most vulnerable young people and families struggle to cope within the confines of our inflexible education system. Chris believes in promoting reform by listening to young people, parents, professionals and academic research. Chris leads on States of Mindâ€™s research projects.</p>
